Juventus midfielder, Sami Khedira has completed a permanent move to Bundesliga side Hertha Berlin after successive Serie A titles during five and a half years in Italy. But he has not featured this season and returns to club football in Germany 11 years after leaving Stuttgart for Real Madrid. "Hertha put in a lot of effort to sign me, for which I am very grateful," said Khedira in a statement on the club website.